s it just me or does that just seem wrong? Why should 1) mages be balanced in terms of their epic and thus give VI an excuse for not fixing the class as a whole and 2) why is every other class NOT given the same level of epic the mages are?</P><P>What I advocate is to balance the classes first without their epics, to make mages and wizards and necros and enchanters worthwhile to play without hoping for some uber-rare item like the epic.  THEN add the epics, powerful and useful for EACH class in their own way.  Doesn't that seem a MUCH better solution than the "lets give mages a powerful epic so we can claim they're balanced" solution?</P><P></P><P>Etadanik the Redeemed<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
