        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I can see where you'e going, Euri, but I still believe that you are thinking about epics in the wrong way.  You say that epics are required to balance you with epic warriors...  Frankly, none of the casting classes, not even wizards(because wizards are ONLY powerful when it comes to raids; in normal groups, their DPS sucks), are balanced with respect to melees, so let's not even go there.  The truth is, you might be right that the MAGE is being balanced with respect to warriors by the epic, but NONE of the other casting classes(chanters, wizards, necros, shamans, etc.) are balanced with respect to melees by their epics, so you're an exception, not the rule.</P><P>At any case, in your eyes mages are balanced by the epic pet, when in truth I think your class is being hampered by the epic pet.  Because other classes think that mages w/epic is so powerful, they don't want to see mages getting any better benefits, but I digress.  </P><P>The way I see it, Euri, is that you THINK that by taking into account epics you are balancing the classes overall, but in truth, you are advocating balancing classes with RESPECT to epics and NOT overall.  An overall balance would leave level 60s without their epics, and with their epics, at about the same place compared to each other.  What you're advocating leaves a level 60 mage without his epic screwed to no ends, while a level 60 mage WITH his epic is finally balanced with a level 60 wizard WITHOUT his epic(because, as I've said, wizard epics can be done without).  So where do you not see the problem? The fact that every level 55+ mage on your server has their epic? I doubt that.  I really do.</P><P><BR>Etadanik the Redeemed<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
