        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=74044&TOPIC_ID=9004&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=necromancer+epic+pet&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Greetings,</P><P>Normally a lurker here but Euri causes me to come forward a bit on this.  Euri, I speak only for myself on this but I feel you are missing a key point or so here.  This thread was about the Necromancer class getting a CLASS ABILITY of a Raid Style pet, not technically an Epic Pet itself as most necro's accept the fact that they got an Epic Dot and that's what's intended.  </P><P>Saying our Class is balanced now takes a bit of work and a bit of drugs but we get by with what we have.  Those of us who have played the game a while know a few tricks to cover for some of our short comings (ie. CC Silk nets = Grasping Root) or have simply accepted that things are this way and gone on with it.  Sure we'd like things different, but sometimes asking to be inspected in light of a fault can lead to other problems.</P><P>Saying that our Epic Pet should be involved in the Class Balance measure makes me post here.  The Mage Epic is difficult and some of the pieces, not just the Crown of Mastery are things people only Dream of seeing.  You add this list of Elemental based spells that you would like for us to have without really looking into what VI would nerf us with to get them.  Those cross well over the line of Class Distinction (blurred already but hey) and would likely result in something *bad* hitting us soon after.  Better for these not to happen at all.</P><P>"quote:</P><P>Epic should NEVER, EVER be considered as an ability of the class. They are a prestigious item, and should have abilities worthy of their position as "epic."<BR>**<BR>Why not? By this logic, warrior weapons shouldn't be considered when considering the class.  And, armor shouldn't be considered. They have to aquire better and better gear, just as a Magician MUST aquire epic to even come near what we should be doing as far as damage goes. "<BR>**</P><P>Etadanik actually hits this more accurately than you do.  The Epic should NOT be considered part of the Class Balance picture but considered more as an Ultimate Class Reward.  Their difficulty in obtaining means that only some of the Class members will ever see them, and some are far more easy to obtain than others.  Some, the Necro Epic for instance has been shown to be actually purchasable in the past, but this is an exception and not the norm.  We as a Class, regardless of Class have certain powers and abilities that define us.  Mages are based upon their pets, necros their DoTs.  An Epic should be added into consideration when you view an *average* player and want to make it better - to enhance it.  A Mage on their own cannot fight without their pet and hope to survive, thus here it defines us.  Necromancers can fight without their pet thus is does not define them, it adds to them.  The difference here means a great deal.  Not about who is more powerful and who should be beaten with a nerf stick but what each Class actually is.</P><P>You go on to compare a Mage against a Warrior at 60 and discuss gear.  One thing you missed here totally is that our gear includes our spellbook as the warrior's includes his armor and weaponry.  Our Epic Pet is our Ultimate Weapon just as the Warrior's Ultimate Weapon is (Insert Uber weapon of the current Expansion here).  Many mages I know currently do not have our Epics and may never get them.  But we'll keep on trying.  Point is that until we finish the Quest we have squat.  Warriors are about the worst comparison you could use as a level 60 warrior could pick up a rusty sword and beat you to death with it where you could do NOTHING without your spellbook.  Remember that our Epic Reward is a spell.  Spells are not gear.  Spells are spells and what defines all pure caster's.  A necro with no spells will last about as long as a mage with no spells in NToV.  Half a second (FD is a spell).</P><P>You say our Epic is not about skill or manpower. It requires being able to tolerate                    weeks upon weeks of tedious killing of the same things. The only difficult part is quiring a crown of elemental mastery from the plane of air. Our uber guilds NEVER do PoA really, and yet three dozen magicians are epic now on my server.  This partially right and so much BS at the same time.  You cannot do several things without assistance, from the Burning Embers in BW to Phinny to Hate to Sky.  We need others to assist, it requires force to reach Isle 7 and trying to get your guild past Isle 5 is a Quest itself.  Our Epic has many road blocks in it that must have been included intentionally.  Quillmane's Cloak not being Lore for one (how many druids farm other peoples Epic items for cash?).</P><P>I've not done the necro bit past 29 so I cannot speak for them without sounding the fool, but I do group with them and I know that a Class Reward Raid Pet is not totally unbalanced when you consider what it would be designed for and what it would be unable to do because of it.  It would likely not be able to be used as a standard hunting pet as either it's cost in materials or mana or environment restrictions would prevent this.  Would it overpower them?  Possibly  possibly not, all depends on implementation.  Would it be interesting to see them try it?  Yes it would.</P><P>Class balance does not always have to be about Nerfing someone else because their better than you.  Class balance is making you the best you can be in the role that you fit into (or that VI decides to hammer you into).</P><P>To everyone else, please do not think that Euri speaks for all mages as it's obvious he/she does not.  I agreed with your lifetap petition before and followed the thread, I agree that this one is interesting and wouldn't be threatened if it came into the world.  Do I think VI's going to let it happen?  Your guess is as good as mine but from seeing necros post beta I would hazzard a no.</P><P>Reah Kitsune'Arcanis<BR>54th Magi  Innoruuk</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
