        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>first off i have a level 60 cleric, with the new mob rod i can i be full mana at the end of a vulak fight you never run out of mana or get summoned i mod down to 10 hp then cheal myself ive never once died<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Only if you never use more than, say, 800 points of mana per fight will a single mod rod fill you to max.  660 of this will come from the rod, youll use some for healing yourself, and the rest will come from meditation, an enchanter mana regeneration buff, and your local Bard.</P><P>If you ever get into a situation where youve just used up your entire bar of mana youll find that mod rods arent quite the godsend that they appear to be.  At 60th level with 200 points of wisdom (without any mana adding gear) you will have 2520 points of mana.  This will require approximately 4 and a half mod rods to regenerate back to full health.  As you most likely have higher than a 200 and have gear that adds mana it will take you more than 4 and a half mod rods.</P><P>Each time a rod is created it costs the Magician 300 mana.  Since the rod gives back 220 points of mana per use the Magician cannot use the rod to become the perpetual mana machine.  Mana regeneration buffs and bards cannot provide mana fast enough, so whats the alternative?</P><P>Twitching, both to the Cleric (mid fight when mod rods have been used) and to the Magician (for more mod rod generation).</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>i did understand you about each necro casting dif dots but trust me 4 necros casting all the dots they have cant match 2 or 3 bane wizards...<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUO